value.title: Secret Service investigating death threats against Pence
value.excerpt: The U.S. Secret Service is investigating death threats against Vice President Mike Pence made by pro-Trump lawyer Lin Wood, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Google, Microsoft, Verizon on Biden Inauguration Committee donor list
value.excerpt: Google, Microsoft, and Verizon are among President-elect Joe Biden's Inauguration Committee donors.

value.title: Trump speech before Capitol riot not enough for impeachment charges: Turley
value.excerpt: Democrats are moving to remove President Trump from office after Wednesday's U.S. Capitol riot, but George Washington University law professor Jonathan Turley said he doesn’t believe Trump committed an impeachable offense.

value.title: Roy Blunt balks at attempt to impeach Trump again: ‘Not going to happen’
value.excerpt: Roy Blunt, R-Mo., Friday balked at the idea of a second impeachment of President Trump.

value.title: Nancy Pelosi, in ‘60 Minutes’ interview, slams Trump as ‘deranged,’ calls for ‘prosecution’
value.excerpt: President Trump is "deranged, unhinged, dangerous," and deserving of prosecution, House Speaker Nancy Pelosi says in an interview scheduled to air Sunday night on "60 Minutes."

value.title: GOP Sen. Toomey: Trump 'committed impeachable offenses'
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Pat Toomey, Pa., said that President Trump “committed impeachable offenses” in his efforts to throw out the results of the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Trump Twitter ban will be ‘exploited’ by ‘enemies' of free speech 'around the world,’ Russian dissident Navaln
value.excerpt: Russian opposition leader Alexey Navalny called Twitter’s ban of President Trump an “unacceptable act of censorship” that could be exploited by oppressive governments around the world.

value.title: Donald Trump Jr.: ‘We are living Orwell’s 1984’ after dad outed from Twitter
value.excerpt: Free-speech no longer exists in America. It died with big tech and what’s left is only there for a chosen few. This is absolute insanity!” he tweeted in response to the news.

value.title: Brit Hume: Twitter's reasons for banning Trump are 'pure editorial judgments'
value.excerpt: Fox News Senior Political Analyst Brit Hume is calling out big social media companies for making the decision to ban President Trump's accounts based on what he says are "pure editorial judgments."

value.title: 'Hang Mike Pence' trends on Twitter after platform suspends Trump for risk of 'incitement of violence'
value.excerpt: Twitter has removed content from "trending" in the past when it violates its rules.

value.title: Nikki Haley says Trump Twitter ban is 'what happens in China'
value.excerpt: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley on Friday reacted to the permanent suspension of President Trump’s Twitter account, describing it as an instance of "silencing" of the kind that happens in communist China.

value.title: Biden says Cruz, Hawley part of ‘big lie’ -- while senators claim they are being called Nazis
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said Friday that Sens. Ted Cruz, R-Texas, and Josh Hawley, R-Mo., should be "flat beaten" in their next elections for their part in spreading "the big lie," a term the senators said was an effort to cast them as Nazis.

value.title: Ilhan Omar says Trump 'will be impeached'
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., vowed on Friday that President Trump would be impeached after this week's riots, which have prompted widespread criticism of the president and his rhetoric following November's election.

value.title: Clyburn accuses resigning Trump Cabinet members of 'running away' from 25th Amendment duty
value.excerpt: House Majority Whip James Clyburn said former Trump Cabinet members Elaine Chao and Betsy DeVos, who resigned in protest of the Capitol riots, were "running away" from their responsibility to invoke the 25th Amendment.

value.title: Kurtz: 'No president has been able to dominate the media, social media, culture more than Trump'
value.excerpt: President Trump is one of the most influential presidents in United States history,” "Media Buzz" host Howard Kurtz said Friday.

value.title: Pelosi says she spoke to Gen. Milley about protecting nuclear codes from Trump
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, D-Calif., said she has spoken to Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Mark Milley about protecting the nuclear codes from an “unhinged president.”

value.title: Ashli Babbitt, rioter fatally shot in DC, was ‘bananas’ over Trump: grandfather
value.excerpt: The Air Force veteran who was fatally shot as she stormed the Capitol was an “excellent patriot” who was a fanatic follower of President Trump, her grandfather said. Ashli Babbitt, 35, of San

value.title: Trump's failure to 'call off mob' at Capitol riots was 'breaking point': Alyssa Farah
value.excerpt: Former White House communications director Alyssa Farah criticized President Trump for his actions Wednesday amid the "heartbreaking" Capitol Hill riots that "crossed a line."

value.title: NY attorney general demands investigation of Trump's, family members' role in fomenting riots
value.excerpt: Letitia James also wants officials to identify and investigate participants in Wednesday's raid on the Capitol

value.title: Trump condemns 'heinous attack' on Capitol, calls for 'healing and reconciliation'
value.excerpt: President Trump condemned Wednesday’s “heinous attack” on the Capitol by his supporters and called for a moment of healing.

value.title: Biden quiet on 25th Amendment calls; tells Pence, Cabinet, Congress to 'act as they see fit'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has stayed mum amid calls from Democrats to invoke the 25th Amendment or pursue articles of impeachment to thwart the last two weeks of the Trump presidency.

value.title: Ex-Israeli Ambassador Danon's Big Idea: Biden should maintain strong stance on Iran, partner with allies
value.excerpt: The Big Idea is a series of Q&As with top lawmakers and figures.

value.title: De Blasio accuses Trump of ‘treason,’ says he should be removed
value.excerpt: New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio on Thursday said President Trump should be removed from office -- and accused him of committing "treason" with his remarks to supporters who went on to storm the Capitol building.

value.title: Capitol rioting 'overshadowed' Trump's accomplishments: Pavlich
value.excerpt: The Capitol Hill rioting and looting after President Trump addressed supporters Wednesday is "overshadowing" his accomplishments of the past four years, Fox News contributor Katie Pavlich argued Thursday.

value.title: Biden says Capitol was stormed by ‘riotous mob,' 'domestic terrorists’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says that the supporters of President Trump who attacked the Capitol on Wednesday were “a riotous mob” and “domestic terrorists.”

value.title: Live Updates: Biden to announce Justice Department picks
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is to announce his nominees for the Justice Department. Biden is also expected to address the rioting on Capitol Hill on Wednesday, which he condemned in strong terms the same day.

value.title: Facebook blocks Trump indefinitely after Capitol riot response
value.excerpt: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg on Thursday said that President Trump’s Facebook and Instagram accounts will be blocked "indefinitely," and for at least the next two weeks before Inauguration Day.

value.title: READ: Pence letter saying he does not have 'unilateral authority' to reject electoral votes
value.excerpt: Pence writes a letter saying he does not have 'unilateral authority' to reject electoral votes

value.title: Pence, Pelosi share 'elbow bump' following Biden certification vote
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi concluded a trying and at times scary joint session of Congress with an elbow bump in the predawn hours of Thursday.

value.title: House members Harris, Allred nearly come to blows during Pennsylvania certification debate: reports
value.excerpt: Tensions on Capitol Hill nearly resulted in fisticuffs early Thursday between a Republican and a Democrat in the U.S. House, according to reporter accounts.
